‚≠ê 1. What is ELB?
ELB (Elastic Load Balancing) distributes incoming traffic across multiple targets:
EC2 instances
Containers
IP addresses
Lambda (ALB only)

Benefits:
High Availability
Fault Tolerance
Automatic scaling
Health checks
SSL/TLS termination
Single point of contact

‚≠ê 2. How ELB Works (Exam Logic)
Client request ‚Üí ELB endpoint
ELB listener receives request
ELB performs health checks
ELB selects healthy target using LB algorithm
Forwards request ‚Üí Target group
Target responds ‚Üí ELB ‚Üí Client

‚≠ê 3. ELB Types (VERY IMPORTANT EXAM TOPIC)
1Ô∏è‚É£ CLB ‚Äì Classic Load Balancer (Legacy)
Layer 4 (TCP/SSL) + Limited L7 (HTTP/HTTPS)
Very basic
No advanced routing
Exam note ‚Üí NOT important, just know it's legacy.

‚úî Use for: Simple TCP or SSL load balancing
‚ùå No host/path-based routing
‚ùå No modern features (WebSockets, HTTP/2, redirects)

2Ô∏è‚É£ NLB ‚Äì Network Load Balancer (Layer 4)
Layer 4 (TCP, UDP, TLS)
Designed for extreme performance
Handles millions of requests per second
Ultra-low latency (microseconds)

Key Features
Supports Elastic IP (EIP) per AZ
Ideal for real-time apps
Static IP support
Can load balance to:
EC2
IPs
Lambda (via TCP passthrough)
Algorithms
Flow hashing
No path/host-based routing

Exam Trigger Words
‚úî ‚ÄúMillions of requests per second‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúStatic IP needed‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúTCP/UDP load balancing‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúLow latency / high throughput‚Äù
üëâ Choose NLB

3Ô∏è‚É£ ALB ‚Äì Application Load Balancer (Layer 7)
Layer 7 (HTTP/HTTPS)
Advanced routing
Best for web applications/microservices

Key Features

Host-based routing (api.example.com ‚Üí service)
Path-based routing (/images, /login, /api/*)
Query/header-based routing
WebSockets support
HTTP/2
Redirects (HTTP ‚Üí HTTPS)
Sticky sessions
Target groups: EC2, IPs, Lambda, containers

Exam Trigger Words
‚úî ‚ÄúMicroservices‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúHTTP headers / URL routing‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúContent-based routing‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúServerless‚Äù
üëâ Choose ALB

4Ô∏è‚É£ GWLB ‚Äì Gateway Load Balancer (Layer 3)
Layer 3 (IP packet level)
Used for virtual appliances like:
Firewalls
IDS/IPS
Deep packet inspection
Security appliances

Key Features
Combines:
Load balancer (scaling appliances)
Gateway (single entry/exit point)
Integrates with GWLB endpoints (GWLBe)

Exam Trigger Words
‚úî ‚ÄúSecurity appliances firewall/IDS/IPS‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúDeep packet inspection‚Äù
‚úî ‚ÄúThird-party VNFs‚Äù
üëâ Choose GWLB

‚≠ê 4. Components (Common Across ELBs)
Load Balancer
Public or internal
Handles listener + provides DNS endpoint
Listeners
Protocol + port mapping

Examples:
ALB: HTTP/HTTPS
NLB: TCP/UDP/TLS
Target Groups
Route traffic to:
EC2
Lambda
Containers
IPs
Health Checks

ALB ‚Üí HTTP-based
NLB ‚Üí TCP-based
GWLB ‚Üí IP-based

‚≠ê 5. Cross-Zone Load Balancing
Distributes traffic across all AZ targets, even if request arrives in one AZ.
Benefits
Better load distribution
Higher availability
Reduced imbalance problems
Limitations
Extra data transfer cost (for NLB if enabled)
More complex architecture
Important Exam Notes
LB Type	Default	Configurable
ALB	ON	Cannot disable
NLB	OFF	Enable manually
CLB	ON	Can disable
‚≠ê 6. ELB Exam Cheat Sheet
Scenario	                                Correct Load Balancer
Content-based routing                      	    ALB
API Gateway alternative (simple HTTP LB)	     ALB
Millions of req/sec                          	NLB
WebSockets                                  	ALB
Static IP required                            NLB
TCP/UDP traffic	                              NLB
Lambda as backend	                            ALB
Firewall / IDS appliance	                    GWLB
Deep packet inspection                       	GWLB
Legacy apps	                                  CLB


1. Which ELB operates at Layer 7 of the OSI model?

A. NLB
B. CLB
C. ALB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: C. ALB
Explanation: ALB is an application layer (Layer 7) load balancer.

2. Which ELB supports content-based routing?

A. NLB
B. ALB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. ALB
Explanation: Only ALB can route based on URL path, host, headers.

3. Which ELB is best for real-time TCP applications needing extremely low latency?

A. CLB
B. ALB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: C. NLB
Explanation: NLB is designed for ultra-low latency and TCP/UDP loads.

4. Which ELB supports static IP addresses?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: NLB provides one Elastic IP per AZ.

5. Which ELB is used for third-party firewall appliances?

A. CLB
B. ALB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: D. GWLB
Explanation: GWLB integrates with virtual appliances like firewalls, IDS/IPS.

6. Which ELB can route requests to AWS Lambda?

A. CLB
B. NLB
C. ALB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: C. ALB
Explanation: ALB supports Lambda targets.

7. Classic Load Balancer is primarily used for:

A. Path-based routing
B. Simple TCP/SSL load balancing
C. WebSockets
D. Streaming

‚úî Answer: B. Simple TCP/SSL load balancing
Explanation: CLB is legacy and supports basic Layer 4/7.

8. Which ELB supports millions of requests per second?

A. GWLB
B. ALB
C. NLB
D. CLB

‚úî Answer: C. NLB
Explanation: NLB is built for extreme performance.

9. Which load balancer supports WebSocket connections?

A. CLB
B. NLB
C. ALB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: C. ALB
Explanation: ALB supports WebSockets and HTTP/2.

10. Which ELB distributes traffic at a packet level (Layer 3)?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. GWLB
D. CLB

‚úî Answer: C. GWLB
Explanation: GWLB works at Layer 3 for IP packet inspection.

‚úÖ PART 2 ‚Äî MEDIUM (SCENARIO MCQs)
11. Your application needs to route traffic to microservices based on URL paths. Which ELB do you choose?

A. CLB
B. ALB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. ALB
Explanation: Path-based routing = ALB.

12. A financial app needs fixed IP addresses and TLS offloading. Best option?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: Only NLB supports static IPs and TLS listeners.

13. You need the lowest latency possible for VoIP traffic. Which ELB?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. GWLB
D. CLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: NLB supports UDP and low-latency communication.

14. You want to perform deep packet inspection before packets reach EC2.

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: D. GWLB
Explanation: GWLB integrates with security appliances.

15. Which ELB uses flow hashing algorithm by default?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: NLB uses flow hash for TCP/UDP connections.

16. For an Auto Scaling group behind ALB, what must be used?

A. Security groups
B. Target groups
C. VPC endpoints
D. EIPs

‚úî Answer: B. Target groups
Explanation: ALB forwards to target groups.

17. Cross-zone Load Balancing for NLB is:

A. On by default
B. Off by default
C. Not supported
D. Always required

‚úî Answer: B. Off by default
Explanation: You must manually enable it.

18. ALB health checks operate at which layer?

A. Layer 3
B. Layer 4
C. Layer 7
D. Layer 2

‚úî Answer: C. Layer 7
Explanation: ALB uses HTTP/HTTPS health checks.

19. Which ELB supports IP-based target registration?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. Both A and B

‚úî Answer: D. Both A and B
Explanation: ALB and NLB can route to IPs.

20. You need sticky sessions for a stateful web app. Which ELB supports it?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. GWLB
D. None

‚úî Answer: A. ALB
Explanation: ALB supports session stickiness cookies.

‚úÖ PART 3 ‚Äî HARD / EXAM-LEVEL SCENARIOS
21. A gaming backend requires UDP and must scale to millions of connections. Choose the best ELB:

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: UDP + high scale = NLB.

22. A multi-AZ app uses ALB and wants even traffic across AZs. What setting?

A. HTTP/2
B. Cross-zone load balancing
C. Pre-warming
D. Sticky sessions

‚úî Answer: B. Cross-zone load balancing
Explanation: ALB has it enabled by default.

23. Which ELB is best for transparent network appliances?

A. CLB
B. NLB
C. GWLB
D. ALB

‚úî Answer: C. GWLB
Explanation: Used for virtual security appliances.

24. A company wants to terminate SSL at the load balancer and forward plain HTTP internally. Which ELB supports SSL offloading?

A. NLB
B. ALB
C. CLB
D. All

‚úî Answer: D. All
Explanation: All ELBs can use HTTPS ‚Üí HTTP termination.

25. You need to route /api/* to one service and /app/* to another. What do you configure?

A. NLB listeners
B. ALB path-based rules
C. CLB listeners
D. GWLB endpoints

‚úî Answer: B. Path-based rules
Explanation: Only ALB supports routing rules.

26. Health checks must test a JSON API endpoint /health. Which LB supports this?

A. NLB
B. CLB
C. ALB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: C. ALB
Explanation: ALB supports L7 health checks with specific paths.

27. Which ELB should you choose for end-to-end encryption where LB must not decrypt?

A. ALB
B. NLB (TLS passthrough)
C. CLB (HTTP listener)
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: NLB supports TLS passthrough.

28. You require fixed IP addresses for incoming traffic. Choose:

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: NLB provides static IPs/EIPs.

29. Which ELB supports Lambda targets?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: A. ALB
Explanation: ALB supports serverless routing.

30. A customer's appliance requires traffic mirroring for security. Which LB integrates best?

A. ALB
B. GWLB
C. NLB
D. CLB

‚úî Answer: B. GWLB
Explanation: GWLB is designed for monitoring & inspection.

‚úÖ PART 4 ‚Äî VERY HARD / TRICKY (Real AWS Exam Style)
31. Company requires IPv4 and IPv6 load balancing at Layer 7. Which ELB?

A. CLB
B. ALB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. ALB
Explanation: ALB fully supports dual-stack + L7 routing.

32. NLB with cross-zone disabled receives 1000 requests in AZ-A but backend instances exist equally in A and B. Where will traffic go?

A. All to AZ-A instances
B. Split equally across A and B
C. All to AZ-B
D. Randomly distributed

‚úî Answer: A. All to AZ-A instances
Explanation: Without cross-zone LB, NLB routes within the AZ.

33. GWLB endpoints are created using which AWS service?

A. S3
B. VPC Endpoint Service
C. Route 53
D. IAM

‚úî Answer: B. VPC Endpoint Service
Explanation: GWLBe is built using VPC endpoint service.

34. An app requires HTTP/2 for clients. Which ELB supports it?

A. ALB only
B. NLB only
C. CLB only
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: A. ALB only
Explanation: ALB supports HTTP/2 on front end.

35. You need to redirect HTTP ‚Üí HTTPS automatically. Which ELB supports redirection rules?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: A. ALB
Explanation: ALB supports redirect actions.

36. Which LB is recommended for microservices running in ECS (Fargate)?

A. CLB
B. ALB
C. NLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. ALB
Explanation: ALB integrates tightly with ECS target groups.

37. A compliance requirement prevents decrypting traffic. What is the correct LB setup?

A. ALB with HTTPS listeners
B. NLB with TLS passthrough
C. CLB with sticky sessions
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: B. NLB with TLS passthrough
Explanation: NLB forwards encrypted traffic directly to targets.

38. Your backend needs the client‚Äôs original IP. Which LB works best?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. None

‚úî Answer: B. NLB
Explanation: NLB preserves the client source IP automatically.

39. For ALB, how do you enable even distribution across all AZs?

A. Enable proxy protocol
B. It is enabled by default
C. Enable NLB routing
D. Change health check protocol

‚úî Answer: B. Enabled by default
Explanation: ALB has cross-zone LB turned ON.

40. Which LB allows you to scale security appliances automatically?

A. ALB
B. NLB
C. CLB
D. GWLB

‚úî Answer: D. GWLB
Explanation: GWLB elastically scales virtual appliances.
